{
  "text": "\u2022 Hyperventilation syndrome: Paresthesia constitutes 35% of presenting complaints in patients with hyperventilation syndrome [CITATION_1] and may begin after as little as threeminute of hyperventilation [CITATION_2] . After increasing the depth or frequency of respiration, www.intechopen.com Paresthesia 72 the alkaline shift produced selectively increases Na + conductance and ectopic discharges in normal cutaneous afferent nerves can be induced [CITATION_3] . Other electrolytes, i.e. magnesium, potassium, chloride, phosphate and bicarbonate, also demonstrated significant changes in concentration [CITATION_4] .",
